# Teaching Tips for Using LLMs in Class 

#### Interacting with AI offers a dynamic and engaging approach to get your students excited about coding, and with thoughtful consideration, your lessons can be seamlessly executed.

## Targeted Assistance

#### Don't have the LLM write entire programs or essays. Instead, use it for specific tasks. 

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">⚙️ Code Generation</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
 Let students provide prompts for the LLM to generate code snippets for specific functionalities.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">📝 Brainstorming</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
 Encourage students to use the LLM to brainstorm ideas for code features or essay topics.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🪲 Bug Identification</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
 Students can input code sections and ask the LLM to identify potential errors or inefficiencies.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">💬 Alternate Phrasing</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  If students struggle with expressing themselves clearly, the LLM can suggest alternative phrasings to improve their writing.
</p></div>
</details>

## Critical Thinking Integration
#### Don't treat LLM outputs as the final word. Teach students to: 

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🎯 Evaluate Accuracy</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Always fact-check information generated by the LLM, especially for factual writing tasks.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🌐 Analyze Bias</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Discuss how LLMs might inherit biases from their training data. Encourage students to be critical of any suggestions that seem biased.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🧠 Explain Reasoning</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Emphasize the importance of understanding the "why" behind code or writing, not just blindly accepting LLM suggestions.
</p></div>
</details>

## Prevent Overreliance and Cheating 
#### Keep your your students in charge of their learning.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🚦 Set Clear Expectations</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Set clear guidelines on appropriate LLM use before introducing it.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">⚙️ Focus on the Learning Process</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
   Emphasize the importance of the learning journey, not just the final product.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">💡 Prioritize Understanding</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
   Structure activities that require students to demonstrate their own understanding, not just the LLM's capabilities.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">✅ Promote Responsible Use</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
   Emphasize the importance of using LLMs ethically and responsibly, avoiding plagiarism and ensuring that the work produced reflects their own understanding and effort.
</p></div>
</details>
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">👍 Peer Review and Discussion</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
   Emphasize the importance of using LLMs ethically and responsibly, avoiding plagiarism and ensuring that the work produced reflects their own understanding and effort.
</p></div>
</details>

